OL,3,C'A new life': The transformational
OL,4,Cpower of organ transplants
OL,6,FHer daughter, Kelsey, agrees that the
OL,7,Fprocedure has been transformational
OL,8,Ffor the family, explaining that Anna-
OL,9,FMaria's concerns went both ways.
OL,11,FShe says, "I don't remember much from
OL,12,Fmy childhood - all I've ever really
OL,13,Fknown is my mum being ill, I've never
OL,14,Freally known her to be well.
OL,16,F"Not having to worry - going to work,
OL,17,Fgoing to school - I always had the
OL,18,Fworry of 'Is she okay? Does she need
OL,19,Fme there?' Just the small things that
OL,20,Fother families probably take for
OL,21,Fgranted that we now appreciate."
