OL,3,C'A new life': The transformational
OL,4,Cpower of organ transplants
OL,6,F"Through the 'opt-out' scheme, it is
OL,7,Fpresumed consent - so if you haven't
OL,8,Factively removed yourself from the
OL,9,Fregister, it is presumed that you have
OL,10,Fmade that decision and you are in
OL,11,Ffavour of organ donation.
OL,13,F"However, by having the conversation,
OL,14,Fyou've solidified that decision-making
OL,15,Ffor your family - that's another
OL,16,Fdecision that they don't have to make
OL,17,Fat what is a very stressful and
OL,18,Fupsetting time," she explains.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G8/9
